  "prompt": "How do I delete snapchat conversation without using clear conversations?",
  "response": "If you want to delete a Snapchat conversation without using the \"Clear Conversations\" feature in the app settings, you can follow these steps. Note that these steps will effectively remove the conversation from your chat list, but the messages may still be visible to the other person unless they delete them on their end as well.\n\n1. **Open Snapchat**: Launch the Snapchat app on your device.\n\n2. **Go to Chats**: Tap on the chat icon at the bottom left of the screen to open your chat list.\n\n3. **Select the Conversation**: Locate the conversation you want to delete. Press and hold on that conversation.\n\n4. **Delete the Conversation**: After pressing and holding, a menu should appear with various options. Look for and select \u201cDelete.\u201d\n\n5. **Confirm Deletion**: Snapchat may prompt you with a confirmation message to ensure you want to delete the conversation. Confirm that you wish to proceed.\n\nIt's important to note that this method only removes the conversation from your device, not from the other person's device. Additionally, saved messages and screenshots may still remain accessible unless both parties delete them. If you intend for both parties not to have any trace of the conversation, you'll need to communicate with the other person to delete the conversation on their end as well.",
